            <p>New York&#44; Feb 28&#47;88<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>In answer to your<lb/> communication I would say that<lb/> I had sent two complete reports<lb/> concerning the standing of the the<lb/> Seminary&#44; one to Mr Max Cohn<lb/> as Secretary of the Trustees and the<lb/> other to Rev Dr H. P. Mendes as Secret&#45;<lb/>&#45;ary of the Advisory Board with the<lb/> idea that these gentlemen would com&#45;<lb/>&#45;municate the same to the respective<lb/> Presidents.  Mr Cohn I know sent<lb/> the report to Mr Blumenthal but<lb/> it seems that up to the date of your<lb/> writing Dr Mendes had not forwarded<lb/> the same to you.  If you will please<lb/> drop me a note to the effect that<lb/> you have not yet received the report<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>from Dr Mendes&#44; I will prepare<lb/> another and send it directly to you.<lb/>  With best thanks for your congrat&#45;<lb/>&#45;ulatory <sic>despatch</sic> at my wedding<lb/> and hoping you will excuse this<lb/> little <sic>inadvertance</sic>&#44; if <sic>inadvertance</sic><lb/> it be I remain with kindest regards<lb/> yours very sincerely<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/> Preceptor<lb/> 327 E. 51<hi rend="sup">st</hi> St<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
